Cool project! Let me build you an enhanced Mood Mirror with multi-person comparison, AI-powered suggestions, and a polished UI.



Here's your enhanced Mood Mirror! Here's what it includes and more ideas to level it up further:

What's built in:

Multi-person mood tracking with a visual comparison bar chart
Mood score (0–100) so you can rank and compare objectively
Group metrics — average score, who's highest, who needs support
Context-aware suggestions per mood (3 per mood state, categorized by type)
"Add person" so you can expand the group dynamically
"Ask Claude" button that sends everyone's current mood to Claude for a personalized plan
Ideas to make it hackathon-winning:

Tracking over time — store mood entries with timestamps so you can show a sparkline trend per person. "Priya has been anxious 3 days in a row" is a much more powerful insight.

Mood triggers — after selecting a mood, ask "what caused this?" with quick-tap options (work, sleep, social, health). This surfaces patterns like "Sam is always stressed on Mondays."

Group mood alerts — if 2+ people are in low mood simultaneously, show a banner like "Group needs a reset — try a 10-minute shared break."

Mood categories — split into energy (high/low) × valence (positive/negative), which gives you Happy, Excited, Calm, Sad, Anxious, Angry as distinct quadrants. Much richer than a single scale.

Weekly report — a shareable summary card showing each person's mood journey that week, their most common mood, and top suggestion.

Anonymous mode — for team use, let people log moods without revealing who's who, showing only group aggregates.


