Here's exactly what was added — zero existing lines were changed:

New route: GET /mood_compare?limit=5

It fetches the user's last N journal entries (default 5, max 20), then:

Trend detection — assigns a numeric score to each mood label (happy=5, calm=4, neutral=3, anxious=2, stressed=1, etc.) and compares the latest entry against the average of the previous ones. Returns "improving", "declining", "stable", or "insufficient_data".
AI suggestions — calls your existing generate_recommendations() with the current mood + trend baked in (e.g. "Stressed (trend: declining)"), so the AI gives trend-aware advice, not generic suggestions.
Returns JSON — so you can call it from your dashboard template via fetch("/mood_compare") without a page reload.
